<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R2-023" project="SprkChat Platform Enhancement R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>SSE Write-Back Enhancement — Stream Write-Back Content as document_stream Events</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, streaming</tags>
    <estimated-effort>medium</estimated-effort>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>BFF API code implementation — enhances WorkingDocumentTools write-back to emit new SSE event types for cross-pane streaming delivery; FR-04 requirement; depends on R2-010 SSE infrastructure</rigor-reason>
    <dependencies>[010]</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Enhance the write-back streaming pipeline so that when `WorkingDocumentTools.WriteBackToWorkingDocumentAsync`
    executes, the content streams to the client via SSE events instead of being returned as a single
    large response.

    **New SSE event types** (add to ChatStreamEvent):
    - `document_stream_start`: emitted once at the beginning of write-back, contains target document info:
      `{ "documentId": "...", "filename": "...", "operation": "replace|append|insert" }`
    - `document_stream_token`: emitted for each content chunk during write-back streaming:
      `{ "content": "...partial text...", "position": N }`
    - `document_stream_end`: emitted once at completion with content integrity hash:
      `{ "documentId": "...", "contentHash": "sha256:...", "totalTokens": N }`

    **Implementation**:
    1. Modify `WorkingDocumentTools.WriteBackToWorkingDocumentAsync` to accept a write-back event
       callback: `Func&lt;ChatStreamEvent, Task&gt; onEvent` parameter
    2. In the chat endpoint streaming pipeline (ChatEndpoints.cs), pass a callback that writes each
       write-back event to the response stream as an SSE frame
    3. Emit `document_stream_start` before AI generation for the write-back content
    4. For each AI response token during write-back mode, emit `document_stream_token` (in addition
       to the regular `token` event so the user sees the content in chat as well)
    5. Compute SHA-256 hash of the final assembled content and emit `document_stream_end`

    **Ordering guarantee**: `document_stream_start` MUST precede all `document_stream_token` events;
    `document_stream_end` MUST be emitted after all tokens and before `done`.

    **Client use**: The SprkChatPane frontend (Phase 3 Task R2-051) forwards `document_stream_*`
    events to `SprkChatBridge` for BroadcastChannel delivery to the AnalysisWorkspace Lexical editor.
    The BFF responsibility is solely correct event emission — frontend routing is Phase 3/4 work.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with Azure AI and Minimal API expertise</role>

  <goal>
    When `WorkingDocumentTools` executes write-back, the SSE stream contains `document_stream_start`,
    `document_stream_token` events with content chunks, and `document_stream_end` with SHA-256 hash.
    Editor updates without page refresh; user sees streaming progress in chat (FR-04).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="Project specification — FR-04 (write-back via SSE + BroadcastChannel), FR-09 (streaming)">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="Project AI context — SprkChatBridge, BroadcastChannel event types, SSE pipeline">projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="WorkingDocumentTools — write-back implementation to enhance with event callback">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs</file>
    <file purpose="ChatEndpoints — SSE emission pipeline from R2-010 to integrate write-back events">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
    <file purpose="SprkChatAgent — tool execution callback pattern">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgent.cs</file>
    <file purpose="SSE streaming canonical pattern">../.claude/patterns/ai/streaming-endpoints.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">MUST NOT cache streaming write-back tokens — `document_stream_token` events are write-through only; cache only the final `document_stream_end` content hash for idempotency verification</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">MUST flow ChatHostContext through write-back operations — target document ID and operation type come from the chat session context, not from hardcoded values</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">MUST NOT log the write-back content in `document_stream_token` events at Info or higher log levels — log only document ID, position index, and token count metadata</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-04">Write-back content MUST stream token-by-token — the client MUST NOT receive a single large write-back payload; progressive streaming is the requirement</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">MUST preserve ordering: document_stream_start → document_stream_token(s) → document_stream_end → done — out-of-order events break client-side document reconstruction</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-sprk-chat-platform-enhancement-r2/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgent.cs</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/streaming-endpoints.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-015-ai-data-governance.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Write-back event callback injection: modify tool method signature to `WriteBackToWorkingDocumentAsync(content, context, Func&lt;ChatStreamEvent, Task&gt; onEvent, CancellationToken ct)` — the endpoint passes its SSE write function as `onEvent`</pattern>
      <pattern>SHA-256 content hash: `Convert.ToHexString(SHA256.HashData(Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(finalContent)))` — prefix with "sha256:" for clarity in the `document_stream_end` payload</pattern>
      <pattern>Position tracking: maintain a `position` counter incremented by `chunk.Length` for each document_stream_token emission — enables client-side ordering verification</pattern>
      <pattern>Dual emission during write-back: each token during write-back mode emits BOTH a `token` event (for display in chat) AND a `document_stream_token` event (for editor routing) — check if this is the desired behavior or if they should be separate</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      SprkChat R1 implemented write-back as a complete operation: the AI generates the full content,
      then sends it to the Lexical editor in one message via BroadcastChannel. R2 streams the write-back
      content token-by-token via SSE, matching the streaming quality of the chat responses.

      The `SprkChatBridge` on the frontend already handles BroadcastChannel events. It needs new event
      type handlers for `document_stream_start/token/end` (Phase 3 Task R2-051). The BFF responsibility
      is ensuring these events are emitted in the correct order with the correct data format.

      The content hash in `document_stream_end` enables the client to verify that the reconstructed
      document content matches what the BFF computed — a lightweight integrity check that prevents
      partial writes from being applied to the editor if SSE events were lost.

      Task R2-010 established the SSE streaming infrastructure and event types. This task adds the
      write-back specific event types on top of that foundation.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-010 (SSE streaming infrastructure and event emission pattern). Sequential.
      Does not depend on R2-011 through R2-022. Task R2-051 (Phase 4 write-back integration) depends
      on this task. Own files: `Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs` (callback addition), `ChatEndpoints.cs`
      (write-back callback wiring), `Models/Ai/Chat/ChatStreamEvent.cs` (new event type discriminators).
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Read `WorkingDocumentTools.cs` to understand the current write-back implementation and how it generates content</step>
    <step order="1">Read `SprkChatAgent.cs` and `ChatEndpoints.cs` to understand how tool execution currently integrates with the SSE stream</step>
    <step order="2">Add `document_stream_start`, `document_stream_token`, and `document_stream_end` event type discriminators to `ChatStreamEvent`</step>
    <step order="3">Modify `WriteBackToWorkingDocumentAsync` method signature to accept `Func&lt;ChatStreamEvent, Task&gt; onEvent` callback parameter</step>
    <step order="4">Implement `document_stream_start` emission at the beginning of the write-back operation</step>
    <step order="5">Implement `document_stream_token` emission for each content chunk during AI generation — track position counter</step>
    <step order="6">Implement SHA-256 hash computation on the final assembled content</step>
    <step order="7">Implement `document_stream_end` emission with hash and total token count</step>
    <step order="8">Update `ChatEndpoints.cs` streaming pipeline to pass the SSE write function as the `onEvent` callback to `WorkingDocumentTools`</step>
    <step order="9">Update `SprkChatAgent` tool invocation to thread the callback through the tool execution path</step>
    <step order="10">Verify event ordering in the stream: start → tokens → end → done (add assertion or test to confirm)</step>
    <step order="11">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="12">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-023 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

