    <tool>git</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/WorkingDocumentTools.cs — enhanced with write-back event callback and document_stream_* event emission</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/ChatStreamEvent.cs — updated with document_stream_start, document_stream_token, document_stream_end event type discriminators</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs — updated to pass SSE write callback to WorkingDocumentTools</artifact>
    <artifact type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgent.cs — updated to thread write-back callback through tool execution</artifact>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">A write-back operation emits `document_stream_start` as the first write-back event in the SSE stream</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Multiple `document_stream_token` events are emitted with sequential position values (0, N, 2N, ...) during write-back content generation</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`document_stream_end` is emitted after all tokens with a non-empty `contentHash` field starting with "sha256:"</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">The ordering is guaranteed: no `document_stream_token` arrives before `document_stream_start`, and `document_stream_end` arrives after all tokens</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`done` event follows `document_stream_end` (write-back events precede stream termination)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No write-back content text appears in logs at Info or higher level (ADR-015)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The exact mechanism for injecting the callback into `WorkingDocumentTools` depends on how the
    tool is currently constructed. If it's instantiated by `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools()`,
    the callback can be passed either as a constructor argument (for the write-back session) or as
    a method parameter. Prefer method parameter injection to avoid making the tool stateful.

    The `position` counter in `document_stream_token` should represent the character offset of the
    chunk in the final assembled content, not an event sequence number. This allows the client to
    reconstruct the document in order even if SSE events arrive out of sequence (though SSE is
    ordered by design).

    Document the `document_stream_*` event payload schemas in `notes/023-writeback-sse-events.md`
    for Phase 3 Task R2-051 (write-back integration) and for the `SprkChatBridge` frontend
    implementation to consume.
  </notes>

